The paper discusses a new architecture for machine translation using an interlingua approach, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and training objectives, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions preliminary translation results and the evaluation of learned representations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), respectively.
